3) Lambda Expressions

⭐11. What is Lambda Expression?
Answer:
Lambda is a short way to implement a functional interface without creating a class. Functional interface is interface with only one abstract method.
Concise way to implement functional interface.

x -> x * 2

⭐12. Why lambda was introduced?
Answer:
To reduce boilerplate code and support functional programming in Java.

